Here's a typical `MauiProgram.cs` setup:

```csharp
using Microsoft.Extensions.Logging;

namespace MyMauiApp;

public static class MauiProgram
{
    public static MauiApp CreateMauiApp()
    {
        var builder = MauiApp.CreateBuilder();
        builder
            .UseMauiApp<App>()
            .ConfigureFonts(fonts =>
            {
                fonts.AddFont("OpenSans-Regular.ttf", "OpenSansRegular");
            });

        // Data service — Singleton: one HttpClient/base URL shared app-wide,
        // avoids socket exhaustion from repeated HttpClient creation.
        builder.Services.AddSingleton<IDataService, DataService>();

        // ViewModels — Transient: each navigation gets a fresh instance
        // with clean state (no stale data between visits).
        builder.Services.AddTransient<MainViewModel>();
        builder.Services.AddTransient<DetailViewModel>();

        // Pages — Transient: paired 1:1 with their ViewModel,
        // so each navigation creates a new page + new VM.
        builder.Services.AddTransient<MainPage>();
        builder.Services.AddTransient<DetailPage>();

        return builder.Build();
    }
}
```

**Why each lifetime:**

| Registration | Lifetime | Reason |
|---|---|---|
| `IDataService` | **Singleton** | Wraps `HttpClient` / shared config. One instance avoids socket exhaustion and lets you cache auth tokens or headers in one place. |
| ViewModels | **Transient** | Each navigation should get a fresh VM — no stale data, no leftover state from a previous visit. |
| Pages | **Transient** | Pages bind to their VM; a fresh page per navigation avoids UI state leaking between visits. |

**When you'd choose differently:**

- **Scoped** — useful in Blazor (per-request), but MAUI has no built-in scope boundary, so it behaves like Singleton. Avoid it unless you create scopes manually.
- **Singleton VM/Page** — only if the page is always on-screen (e.g., a shell tab that should preserve scroll position).
- If `DataService` held per-user mutable state that needs resetting, you might make it Transient and inject `IHttpClientFactory` instead (the factory itself is Singleton).
